{"parse":{"title":"Intracorporate Conspiracy Doctrine","pageid":55748823,"revid":809792805,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Intracorporate Conspiracy Doctrine</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Common-law\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Common-law\">common-law</a> doctrine in American law that states that members of a corporation, such as employees, cannot be held to have conspired among themselves, because the corporation and its agents constitute a single actor for purposes of law. Therefore, it is reasoned that there is no plurality of actors needed to constitute a conspiracy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> However, the doctrine is held not to apply in some areas of law. Furthermore, in some areas of law, is not uniformly applied the same way throughout the federal circuits.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Intracorporate_Conspiracy_Doctrine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Prisbe, John T. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://scholarworks.law.ubalt.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1471&amp;context=ublr\">\"Comments: The Intracorporate Conspiracy Doctrine\"</a>. <i>University of Baltimore Law Review</i>. <b>16</b> (3).</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=University+of+Baltimore+Law+Review&amp;rft.atitle=Comments%3A+The+Intracorporate+Conspiracy+Doctrine&amp;rft.volume=16&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.aulast=Prisbe&amp;rft.aufirst=John+T&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fscholarworks.law.ubalt.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1471%26context%3Dublr&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntracorporate+Conspiracy+Doctrine\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bna.com/civil-conspiracy-parent-n17179891713\">\"Civil Conspiracy Between Parent Corporations and Wholly Owned Subsidiaries: A National Survey\"</a>. <i>www.bna.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-11-09</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.bna.com&amp;rft.atitle=Civil+Conspiracy+Between+Parent+Corporations+and+Wholly+Owned+Subsidiaries%3A+A+National+Survey&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bna.com%2Fcivil-conspiracy-parent-n17179891713&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntracorporate+Conspiracy+Doctrine\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.jha.com/us/blog/?blogID=254\">\"jha.com - Joseph Hage Aaronson LLC - Complex Lit Blog\"</a>. <i>www.jha.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-11-09</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.jha.com&amp;rft.atitle=jha.com+-+Joseph+Hage+Aaronson+LLC+-+Complex+Lit+Blog&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jha.com%2Fus%2Fblog%2F%3FblogID%3D254&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntracorporate+Conspiracy+Doctrine\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://nahmodlaw.com/2012/10/08/section-1983-and-the-intracorporate-conspiracy-doctrine/\">\"Section 1983 and the Intracorporate Conspiracy Doctrine\"</a>. <i>Nahmod Law</i>. 2012-10-08<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-11-09</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Nahmod+Law&amp;rft.atitle=Section+1983+and+the+Intracorporate+Conspiracy+Doctrine&amp;rft.date=2012-10-08&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnahmodlaw.com%2F2012%2F10%2F08%2Fsection-1983-and-the-intracorporate-conspiracy-doctrine%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIntracorporate+Conspiracy+Doctrine\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Scale_of_justice_2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Scale_of_justice_2.svg/22px-Scale_of_justice_2.svg.png\" width=\"22\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Scale_of_justice_2.svg/33px-Scale_of_justice_2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.o